HEADWORD: out and out
<hw>out and out</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<def>Without any reservation or disguise; downright; plain; unqualified;
absolute; <as>as, an <ex>out and out</ex> villain; an
<ex>out-and-out</ex> lie</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flat-out, outright.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

